Around 1809 Daniel Pierpont purchased the Pierpont Homestead at 29 State Street North Haven — a Georgian Colonial built 1785 by Stephen Jacobs to which he added a rear addition in 1846. The homestead and the adjacent store run by son Rufus for over a hundred years became 'the center of life at the Pines Bridge in North Haven' and is today a local historic district. The house does not face State Street because the road originally curved to a ford across the river."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Born and died North Haven, age seventy-six","body":"Daniel Pierpont was born May 16, 1775 in North Haven Connecticut and died there November 16, 1851 at age seventy-six, buried at Old Cemetery North Haven. He had married Esther Humiston on September 26, 1799 — she outlived him by thirteen years, dying August 17, 1864 in New Haven at age ninety. Their seven children were Bede, Elias, Esther/Stiles, Harriet, Sally, Jared, and Rufus."}],"slug":"daniel-pierpont-1775"},"X00468":{"id":"X00468","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1774},"death":{"year":1864},"gender":"female","parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00877","date_year":1799,"date_month":9,"date_day":26,"children_ids":["HD1444","HD1445","HD1446","HD1447","HD1448","HD1449","HD1450"]}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Esther Humiston","first_name":"Esther","maiden_name":"Humiston","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"esther-humiston-1774"},"HD1444":{"id":"HD1444","has_descendants_docume